17 (c) On July 1, 2026, or as soon thereafter as moneys are available,
18 $50,000,000 shall be transferred by the director of accounts and reports
19 from the state general fund to the Kansas educational building fund. On
20 July 1, 2027, and on July 1 each year thereafter, or as soon thereafter as
21 moneys are available, an amount equal to the amount pursuant to this
22 subsection for the immediately preceding year plus 2% of $50,000,000
23 shall be transferred by the director of accounts and reports from the state
24 general fund to the Kansas educational building fund.
25 Sec. 3. K.S.A. 76-6b04 is hereby amended to read as follows: 76-
26 6b04. (a) There is hereby levied an annual permanent state tax in the year
27 2025 a state tax of 0.5 mill upon all tangible property in this state which
28 that is subject to ad valorem taxation. The tax levy shall be .3 mill in the
29 year 2003 and .5 mill in the year 2004 and each year thereafter until
30 changed by statute. The tax levy shall be in addition to all other state tax
31 levies authorized by law. The tax levy shall be for the use and benefit of
32 state institutions caring for persons who are mentally ill, retarded, visually
33 handicapped, with a handicapping hearing loss or tubercular or state
34 institutions caring for children who are deprived, wayward, miscreant,
35 delinquent, children in need of care or juvenile offenders and who are in
36 need of residential care or treatment, or institutions designed primarily to
37 provide vocational rehabilitation for handicapped persons. As used in this
38 section, "state institutions" shall include, but not be limited to, those
39 institutions under the authority of the commissioner of juvenile justice.
40 The proceeds of such tax levy shall be apportioned in accordance with this
41 act.
42 (b) The county treasurer of each county shall make the proceeds of
43 the tax levy provided for in this section available to the state treasurer

