5 Sec. 5. K.S.A. 76-6b11 is hereby amended to read as follows: 76-
6 6b11. (a) Except as provided in subsection (e), On July 1 of each year, the
7 director of accounts and reports shall record a debit to the state treasurer's
8 receivables for the Kansas educational building fund, the state institutions
9 building fund and the state general fund and shall record a corresponding
10 credit to each such fund in an amount equal to 95% of the amount credited
11 respectively to each such fund during the immediately preceding fiscal
12 year, except that such amount shall be proportionally adjusted with respect
13 to any such fund in any fiscal year for any change in the tax levy rate for
14 any such fund.
15 (b) All taxes received by the state treasurer under K.S.A. 76-6b01,
16 and 76-6b04 and section 15 [L. 2003, ch. 146, § 15], and amendments
17 thereto, and the provisions of section 15 of chapter 146 of the 2003
18 Session Laws of Kansas during the current fiscal year shall be deposited in
19 the state treasury to the credit of the Kansas educational building fund, the
20 state institutions building fund and the state general fund, respectively, and
21 shall reduce the amount debited and credited to such funds under
22 subsection (a).
23 (c) On June 30 of each year, the director of accounts and reports shall
24 adjust the amounts debited and credited to the state treasurer's receivables
25 and to the Kansas educational building fund, the state institutions building
26 fund and the state general fund pursuant to this section, to reflect the taxes
27 actually received by the state treasurer and deposited during the fiscal year
28 in the state treasury to the credit of each such fund.
29 (d) The director of accounts and reports shall notify the state treasurer
30 of all amounts debited and credited to the Kansas educational building
31 fund, the state institutions building fund and the state general fund
32 pursuant to this section and all reductions and adjustments thereto made
33 pursuant to this section. The state treasurer shall enter all such amounts
34 debited and credited and shall make reductions and adjustments thereto on
35 the books and records kept and maintained for such funds by the state
36 treasurer in accordance with the notice thereof.
37 (e) On October 1, 2003, the director of accounts and reports shall
38 make such adjustments and amendments as may be required to reflect and
39 account for the property tax imposed by K.S.A. 79-2976 as if such tax had
40 been in effect on July 1, 2003.The provisions of this section shall expire on
41 June 30, 2026.
